1 timber to processing facilities; and
2 WHEREAS, his professionalism and adherence to Louisiana's Forestry Best
3 Management Practices are well known among landowners, enhancing his reputation for
4 quality work and placing him in high demand among timberland owners.
5 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
6 commend and congratulate John Keith of AllState Land and Timber in Haughton, Louisiana,
7 upon being named the "Louisiana Outstanding Logger of the Year" and does hereby
8 recognize his dedication to the logging industry and his tireless efforts to promote safe and
9 efficient logging practices that benefit the environment and the economy of the state of
10 Louisiana.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to John
12 Keith.
